fastPathQOSACL.name: fastPathQOSACL

revisions.description: Added support for ACL Redirect to External Agent action attribute.
Added support for ACL Rate Limiting rule attribute.
Added support for ACL rule logging and trap notification.

fastPathQOSACL.description: The MIB definitions for Quality of Service - ACL Flex package.

EtypeValue.name: EtypeValue
EtypeValue.description: Ethertype value of a packet. The allowed value is 0x0600 to 0xFFFF.

Ipv6AddressPrefix.name: Ipv6AddressPrefix
Ipv6AddressPrefix.description: This data type is used to model IPv6 address prefixes. This is a binary string of up to 16 octets in network byte-order.

AclBurstSize.name: AclBurstSize
AclBurstSize.description: The number of kilobytes (Kbytes) in a packet that may be sent in a traffic stream without regard for other traffic streams.

aclNamedIpv4IndexNextFree.name: aclNamedIpv4IndexNextFree
aclNamedIpv4IndexNextFree.description: This object contains an unused value for the aclIndex to be used when creating a new named IPv4 ACL. A value of zero zero indicates the ACL table is full.

aclIndex.name: aclIndex
aclIndex.description: The IP ACL table index this instance is associated with.

aclStatus.name: aclStatus
aclStatus.description: Status of this instance. Entries can not be deleted until all rows in the aclIfTable and aclRuleTable with corresponding values of aclIndex have been deleted. active(1) - this ACL instance is active createAndGo(4) - set to this value to create an instance destroy(6) - set to this value to delete an instance

aclName.name: aclName
aclName.description: The name of this IPv4 ACL entry, which must consist of 1 to 31 alphanumeric characters and uniquely identify this IPv4 ACL. An existing IPv4 ACL can be renamed by setting this object to a new name. This object must be set to complete a new IPv4 ACL row instance.

aclIfTable.name: aclIfTable
aclIfTable.description: A table of ACL interface instances per direction.

aclIfIndex.name: aclIfIndex
aclIfIndex.description: The interface to which this ACL instance applies.

aclIfDirection.name: aclIfDirection
aclIfDirection.description: The interface direction to which this ACL instance applies.

aclIfSequence.name: aclIfSequence
aclIfSequence.description: The relative evaluation sequence of this ACL for this interface and direction. When multiple ACLs are allowed for a given interface and direction, the sequence number determines the order in which the list of ACLs are evaluated, with lower sequence numbers given higher precedence. The sequence number value is arbitrary, but must be a unique non-zero value for a given interface and direction. Setting this object to an existing sequence number value for a given interface and direction causes the ACL corresponding to that value to be replaced with this ACL.

aclIfAclType.name: aclIfAclType
aclIfAclType.description: The type of this ACL, which is used to interpret the aclIfId object value. Each type of ACL uses its own numbering scheme for identification (see aclIfAclId object for details). The aclIfAclId object must be specified along with this object.

aclIfAclId.name: aclIfAclId
aclIfAclId.description: The ACL identifier value, which is interpreted based on the aclIfType object. For the IP ACLs, the actual ACL number is its identifier as follows: IP standard ranges from 1-99, while IP extended ranges from 100-199. Here, aclIfAclId represents aclIndex. The MAC ACLs use an internally-generated index value that is assigned when the ACL is created.Here, aclIfAclId represents aclMacIndex. The IPv6 ACLs use an internally-generated index value that is assigned when the ACL is created.Here, aclVlanAclId represents aclIpv6Index. The aclIfType object must be specified along with this object.

aclIfStatus.name: aclIfStatus
aclIfStatus.description: Status of this instance. active(1) - this ACL interface instance is active createAndGo(4) - set to this value to assign an ACL to an interface and direction destroy(6) - set to this value to remove an ACL from an interface and direction

aclRuleTable.name: aclRuleTable
aclRuleTable.description: A table of IP ACL Rule instances.

aclRuleEntry.name: aclRuleEntry
aclRuleEntry.description: A table of IP ACL Classification Rules

aclRuleIndex.name: aclRuleIndex
aclRuleIndex.description: The index of this rule instance within an IP ACL.

aclRuleAction.name: aclRuleAction
aclRuleAction.description: The type of action this rule should perform.

aclRuleProtocol.name: aclRuleProtocol
aclRuleProtocol.description: icmp - 1 igmp - 2 ip - 4 tcp - 6 udp - 17 All values from 1 to 255 are valid.

aclRuleSrcIpAddress.name: aclRuleSrcIpAddress
aclRuleSrcIpAddress.description: The Source IP Address used in the ACL Classification.

aclRuleSrcIpMask.name: aclRuleSrcIpMask
aclRuleSrcIpMask.description: The Source IP Mask used in the ACL Classification. This mask is expressed using wild-card notation,which is the 1's compliment of traditional Subnet Masks. Here, the 'Don't care bits' are represented by binary 1's and 'Do care bits' are represented by binary 0's.

aclRuleSrcL4Port.name: aclRuleSrcL4Port
aclRuleSrcL4Port.description: The Source Port Number (Layer 4) used in the ACL Classification.

aclRuleSrcL4PortRangeStart.name: aclRuleSrcL4PortRangeStart
aclRuleSrcL4PortRangeStart.description: The Source Port Number(Layer 4) range start.

aclRuleSrcL4PortRangeEnd.name: aclRuleSrcL4PortRangeEnd
aclRuleSrcL4PortRangeEnd.description: The Source Port Number(Layer 4) range end.

aclRuleDestIpAddress.name: aclRuleDestIpAddress
aclRuleDestIpAddress.description: The Destination IP Address used in the ACL Classification.

aclRuleDestIpMask.name: aclRuleDestIpMask
aclRuleDestIpMask.description: The Destination IP Mask used in the ACL Classification. This mask is expressed using wild-card notation,which is the 1's compliment of traditional Subnet Masks. Here, the 'Don't care bits' are represented by binary 1's and 'Do care bits' are represented by binary 0's.

aclRuleDestL4Port.name: aclRuleDestL4Port
aclRuleDestL4Port.description: The Destination Port (Layer 4) used in ACl classification.

aclRuleDestL4PortRangeStart.name: aclRuleDestL4PortRangeStart
aclRuleDestL4PortRangeStart.description: The Destination Port (Layer 4) starting range used in ACL classification.

aclRuleDestL4PortRangeEnd.name: aclRuleDestL4PortRangeEnd
aclRuleDestL4PortRangeEnd.description: The Destination Port (Layer 4) ending range used in ACL classification.

aclRuleIPDSCP.name: aclRuleIPDSCP
aclRuleIPDSCP.description: The Differentiated Services Code Point value.

aclRuleIpPrecedence.name: aclRuleIpPrecedence
aclRuleIpPrecedence.description: The Type of Service (TOS) IP Precedence value.

aclRuleIpTosBits.name: aclRuleIpTosBits
aclRuleIpTosBits.description: The Type of Service (TOS) Bits value.

aclRuleIpTosMask.name: aclRuleIpTosMask
aclRuleIpTosMask.description: The Type of Service (TOS) Mask value.

aclRuleStatus.name: aclRuleStatus
aclRuleStatus.description: Status of this instance. active(1) - this ACL Rule is active createAndGo(4) - set to this value to create an instance destroy(6) - set to this value to delete an instance

aclRuleAssignQueueId.name: aclRuleAssignQueueId
aclRuleAssignQueueId.description: Queue identifier to which all inbound packets matching this ACL rule are directed. This object defaults to the standard queue assignment for user priority 0 traffic per the IEEE 802.1D specification based on the number of assignable queues in the system: 1-3 queues: 0 4-7 queues: 1 8 queues: 2 This default assignment is static and is not influenced by other system configuration changes.

aclRuleRedirectIntf.name: aclRuleRedirectIntf
aclRuleRedirectIntf.description: A non-zero value indicates the external ifIndex to which all inbound packets matching this ACL rule are directed. A value of zero means packet redirection is not in effect, which is the default value of this object. Note that packet redirection and mirroring (aclRuleMirrorIntf object) are mutually-exclusive rule attributes.

aclRuleMatchEvery.name: aclRuleMatchEvery
aclRuleMatchEvery.description: Flag to indicate that the ACL rule is defined to match on every IP packet, regardless of content.

aclRuleMirrorIntf.name: aclRuleMirrorIntf
aclRuleMirrorIntf.description: A non-zero value indicates the external ifIndex to which all inbound packets matching this ACL rule are copied. A value of zero means packet mirroring is not in effect, which is the default value of this object. Note that packet mirroring and redirection (aclRuleRedirectIntf object) are mutually-exclusive rule attributes.

aclRuleLogging.name: aclRuleLogging
aclRuleLogging.description: Flag to indicate that the ACL rule is being logged. A hardware count of the number of times this rule is hit is reported via the aclTrapRuleLogEvent notification. This object may be supported for an aclRuleAction setting of permit(1) and/or deny(2), depending on the ACL feature capabilities of the device.

aclRuleTimeRangeName.name: aclRuleTimeRangeName
aclRuleTimeRangeName.description: Name of the time range, that the ACL rule has referenced.It must start with alphabet and shall consist of 1 to 31 alphanumeric characters.

aclRuleTimeRangeStatus.name: aclRuleTimeRangeStatus
aclRuleTimeRangeStatus.description: Flag that indicates the ACL rule status. If the status is active, it implies that the ACL rule is in effect. If the status is inactive, it implies that the ACL rule is not in effect.

aclRuleRateLimitCrate.name: aclRuleRateLimitCrate
aclRuleRateLimitCrate.description: Committed rate attribute statement value, specified in kbps.

aclRuleRateLimitCburst.name: aclRuleRateLimitCburst
aclRuleRateLimitCburst.description: Committed burst size attribute statement value, specified in kbytes.

aclRuleIcmpType.name: aclRuleIcmpType
aclRuleIcmpType.description: ACL rule matches on the specified ICMP type. All values from 1 to 255 are valid.

aclRuleIcmpCode.name: aclRuleIcmpCode
aclRuleIcmpCode.description: ACL rule matches on the specified ICMP code. All values from 1 to 255 are valid.

aclRuleIgmpType.name: aclRuleIgmpType
aclRuleIgmpType.description: ACL rule matches on the specified IGMP type. All values from 1 to 255 are valid.

aclRuleEstablished.name: aclRuleEstablished
aclRuleEstablished.description: Flag to indicate the ACL rule to match on TCP packets that has either RST or ACK bits set in the TCP header

aclRuleFragments.name: aclRuleFragments
aclRuleFragments.description: Flag to indicate the ACL rule to match if the packet is fragmented

aclMacIndexNextFree.name: aclMacIndexNextFree
aclMacIndexNextFree.description: This object contains an unused value for the aclMacIndex to be used when creating a new MAC ACL. A value of zero zero indicates the ACL table is full.

aclMacTable.name: aclMacTable
aclMacTable.description: A table of MAC ACL instances.

aclMacIndex.name: aclMacIndex
aclMacIndex.description: The MAC ACL table index this instance is associated with. When creating a new MAC ACL, refer to the aclMacIndexNextFree object to determine the next available aclMacIndex to use.

aclMacName.name: aclMacName
aclMacName.description: The name of this MAC ACL entry, which must consist of 1 to 31 alphanumeric characters and uniquely identify this MAC ACL. An existing MAC ACL can be renamed by setting this object to a new name. This object must be set to complete a new MAC ACL row instance.

aclMacStatus.name: aclMacStatus
aclMacStatus.description: Status of this instance. ACL MAC entries can not be deleted until all rows in the aclIfTable and aclRuleTable with corresponding values of aclMacIndex have been deleted. active(1) - this ACL instance is active createAndGo(4) - set to this value to create an instance destroy(6) - set to this value to delete an instance The aclMacName object must be set to complete this row instance.

aclMacRuleTable.name: aclMacRuleTable
aclMacRuleTable.description: A table of layer 2 MAC ACL Rule instances.

aclMacRuleEntry.name: aclMacRuleEntry
aclMacRuleEntry.description: A table of layer 2 MAC ACL Classification Rules

aclMacRuleIndex.name: aclMacRuleIndex
aclMacRuleIndex.description: The index of this rule instance within an MAC ACL.

aclMacRuleAction.name: aclMacRuleAction
aclMacRuleAction.description: The type of action this MAC ACL rule should perform.

aclMacRuleCos.name: aclMacRuleCos
aclMacRuleCos.description: The Class of Service (COS) used in the MAC ACL Classification. This is the three-bit user priority field in the 802.1Q tag header of a tagged Ethernet frame. For frames containing a double VLAN tag, this field is located in the first/outer tag.

aclMacRuleCos2.name: aclMacRuleCos2
aclMacRuleCos2.description: The Secondary Class of Service (COS2) used in the MAC ACL Classification. This is the three-bit user priority field in the second/inner 802.1Q tag header of a double VLAN tagged Ethernet frame.

aclMacRuleDestMacAddr.name: aclMacRuleDestMacAddr
aclMacRuleDestMacAddr.description: The Destination MAC address used in the MAC ACL Classification.

aclMacRuleDestMacMask.name: aclMacRuleDestMacMask
aclMacRuleDestMacMask.description: The Destination MAC address mask used in the MAC ACL Classification. This mask value identifies the portion of the aclMacRuleDestMacAddr that is compared against a packet. A non-contiguous mask value is permitted.

aclMacRuleEtypeKey.name: aclMacRuleEtypeKey
aclMacRuleEtypeKey.description: The Ethertype keyword used in the MAC ACL Classification. A keyword of custom(1) requires that the aclMacRuleEtypeValue object also be set.

aclMacRuleEtypeValue.name: aclMacRuleEtypeValue
aclMacRuleEtypeValue.description: The Ethertype custom value used in the MAC ACL Classification. This object is only valid if the aclMacRuleEtypeKey is set to custom(1). The allowed value for this object is 0x0600 to 0xFFFF (1536 to 65535).

aclMacRuleSrcMacAddr.name: aclMacRuleSrcMacAddr
aclMacRuleSrcMacAddr.description: The Source MAC address used in the MAC ACL Classification.

aclMacRuleSrcMacMask.name: aclMacRuleSrcMacMask
aclMacRuleSrcMacMask.description: The Source MAC address mask used in the MAC ACL Classification. This mask value identifies the portion of the aclMacRuleSrcMacAddr that is compared against a packet. A non-contiguous mask value is permitted.

aclMacRuleVlanId.name: aclMacRuleVlanId
aclMacRuleVlanId.description: The VLAN ID value used in the MAC ACL Classification. The VLAN ID field is defined as the 12-bit VLAN identifier in the 802.1Q tag header of a tagged Ethernet frame. This is contained in the first/outer tag of a double VLAN tagged frame.

aclMacRuleVlanIdRangeStart.name: aclMacRuleVlanIdRangeStart
aclMacRuleVlanIdRangeStart.description: The VLAN ID range start value used in the MAC ACL Classification. Setting this value greater than the current aclMacRuleVlanIdRangeEnd changes the VLAN ID range end to the same value as the range start. The VLAN ID field is defined as the 12-bit VLAN identifier in the 802.1Q tag header of a tagged Ethernet frame. This is contained in the first/outer tag of a double VLAN tagged frame.

aclMacRuleVlanIdRangeEnd.name: aclMacRuleVlanIdRangeEnd
aclMacRuleVlanIdRangeEnd.description: The VLAN ID range end value used in the MAC ACL Classification. Setting this value less than the current aclMacRuleVlanIdRangeStart changes the VLAN ID range start to the same value as the range end. The VLAN ID field is defined as the 12-bit VLAN identifier in the 802.1Q tag header of a tagged Ethernet frame. This is contained in the first/outer tag of a double VLAN tagged frame.

aclMacRuleVlanId2.name: aclMacRuleVlanId2
aclMacRuleVlanId2.description: The Secondary VLAN ID value used in the MAC ACL Classification. The Secondary VLAN ID field is defined as the 12-bit VLAN identifier in the second/inner 802.1Q tag header of a double VLAN tagged Ethernet frame.

aclMacRuleVlanId2RangeStart.name: aclMacRuleVlanId2RangeStart
aclMacRuleVlanId2RangeStart.description: The Secondary VLAN ID range start value used in the MAC ACL Classification. Setting this value greater than the current aclMacRuleVlanId2RangeEnd changes the Secondary VLAN ID range end to the same value as the range start. The Secondary VLAN ID field is defined as the 12-bit VLAN identifier in the second/inner 802.1Q tag header of a double VLAN tagged Ethernet frame.

aclMacRuleVlanId2RangeEnd.name: aclMacRuleVlanId2RangeEnd
aclMacRuleVlanId2RangeEnd.description: The Secondary VLAN ID range end value used in the MAC ACL Classification. Setting this value less than the current aclMacRuleVlanId2RangeStart changes the Secondary VLAN ID range start to the same value as the range end. The Secondary VLAN ID field is defined as the 12-bit VLAN identifier in the second/inner 802.1Q tag header of a double VLAN tagged Ethernet frame.

aclMacRuleStatus.name: aclMacRuleStatus
aclMacRuleStatus.description: Status of this instance. active(1) - this ACL Rule is active createAndGo(4) - set to this value to create an instance destroy(6) - set to this value to delete an instance

aclMacRuleAssignQueueId.name: aclMacRuleAssignQueueId
aclMacRuleAssignQueueId.description: Queue identifier to which all inbound packets matching this MAC ACL rule are directed. This object defaults to the standard queue assignment for user priority 0 traffic per the IEEE 802.1D specification based on the number of assignable queues in the system: 1-3 queues: 0 4-7 queues: 1 8 queues: 2 This default assignment is static and is not influenced by other system configuration changes.

aclMacRuleRedirectIntf.name: aclMacRuleRedirectIntf
aclMacRuleRedirectIntf.description: A non-zero value indicates the external ifIndex to which all inbound packets matching this MAC ACL rule are directed. A value of zero means packet redirection is not in effect, which is the default value of this object. Note that packet redirection and mirroring (aclMacRuleMirrorIntf object) are mutually-exclusive rule attributes.

aclMacRuleMatchEvery.name: aclMacRuleMatchEvery
aclMacRuleMatchEvery.description: Flag to indicate that the MAC ACL rule is defined to match all packets, regardless of Ethertype.

aclMacRuleMirrorIntf.name: aclMacRuleMirrorIntf
aclMacRuleMirrorIntf.description: A non-zero value indicates the external ifIndex to which all inbound packets matching this MAC ACL rule are copied. A value of zero means packet mirroring is not in effect, which is the default value of this object. Note that packet mirroring and redirection (aclMacRuleRedirectIntf object) are mutually-exclusive rule attributes.

aclMacRuleLogging.name: aclMacRuleLogging
aclMacRuleLogging.description: Flag to indicate that the ACL rule is being logged. A hardware count of the number of times this rule is hit is reported via the aclTrapRuleLogEvent notification. This object may be supported for an aclMacRuleAction setting of permit(1) and/or deny(2), depending on the ACL feature capabilities of the device.

aclMacRuleTimeRangeName.name: aclMacRuleTimeRangeName
aclMacRuleTimeRangeName.description: Name of the time range, that the ACL rule has referenced.It must start with alphabet and shall consist of 1 to 31 alphanumeric characters.

aclMacRuleTimeRangeStatus.name: aclMacRuleTimeRangeStatus
aclMacRuleTimeRangeStatus.description: Flag that indicates the ACL rule status. If the status is active, it implies that the ACL rule is in effect. If the status is inactive, it implies that the ACL rule is not in effect.

aclMacRuleRateLimitCrate.name: aclMacRuleRateLimitCrate
aclMacRuleRateLimitCrate.description: Committed rate attribute statement value, specified in kbps.

aclMacRuleRateLimitCburst.name: aclMacRuleRateLimitCburst
aclMacRuleRateLimitCburst.description: Committed burst size attribute statement value, specified in kbytes.

aclTrapRuleIndex.name: aclTrapRuleIndex
aclTrapRuleIndex.description: The index of an ACL rule instance. Used by aclTrapRuleLogEvent trap.

aclTrapRuleAction.name: aclTrapRuleAction
aclTrapRuleAction.description: The type of action this rule should perform, either permit(1) or deny(2). Used by aclTrapRuleLogEvent trap.

aclTrapRuleHitCount.name: aclTrapRuleHitCount
aclTrapRuleHitCount.description: Number of times the ACL rule was hit during the most recent logging interval. Used by aclTrapRuleLogEvent trap.

aclTrapFlag.name: aclTrapFlag
aclTrapFlag.description: ACL Trap Flag - Enables or disables ACL trap generation. When this value is set to enable(1), ACL traps are sent from the switch when they occur.

aclTrapRuleTimeRangeName.name: aclTrapRuleTimeRangeName
aclTrapRuleTimeRangeName.description: Name of the time range on which there is a notification received. Used by aclTrapRuleTimeRangeEvent.

aclTrapRuleTimeRangeNotification.name: aclTrapRuleTimeRangeNotification
aclTrapRuleTimeRangeNotification.description: Flag to indicate the type of time range notification received. Used by aclTrapRuleTimeRangeEvent.

aclTrapRuleInstallationStatus.name: aclTrapRuleInstallationStatus
aclTrapRuleInstallationStatus.description: Value specifies the status of the ACL Rule installed in hardware as activated/deactivated. Used by aclTrapRuleTimeRangeEvent.

aclTrapRuleLogEvent.name: aclTrapRuleLogEvent
aclTrapRuleLogEvent.description: This trap is generated on a periodic basis to indicate that an ACL rule configured for logging was actively used by hardware to take action on one or more packets. The aclTrapRuleHitCount denotes the number of times this rule was hit during the most recent logging interval. ACL Trap generation requires that the aclTrapFlag object be set to enable(1).

aclTrapRuleTimeRangeEvent.name: aclTrapRuleTimeRangeEvent
aclTrapRuleTimeRangeEvent.description: This trap is generated when there is a time range notification received on any Time based ACL rule. The aclTrapRuleTimeRangeName denotes the time range name associated with the ACL Rule, aclTrapRuleTimeRangeNotification indicates the type of notification received and aclTrapRuleInstallationStatus indicates the installation status of ACL Rule in hardware. When activate notification is received ACL rule is activated in the hardware. When deactivate notifcation is received ACL rule is deactivated in the hardware. When delete notification is received ACL rule is activated in the hardware, if it is already not activated. ACL Trap generation requires the aclTrapFlag object be set to enable(1).

aclIpv6IndexNextFree.name: aclIpv6IndexNextFree
aclIpv6IndexNextFree.description: This object contains an unused value for the aclIPv6Index to be used when creating a new IPv6 ACL. A value of zero zero indicates the ACL table is full.

aclIpv6Table.name: aclIpv6Table
aclIpv6Table.description: A table of Ipv6 ACL instances.

aclIpv6Index.name: aclIpv6Index
aclIpv6Index.description: The IPv6 ACL table index this instance is associated with. When creating a new IPv6 ACL, refer to the aclIPv6IndexNextFree object to determine the next available aclIpv6Index to use.

aclIpv6Name.name: aclIpv6Name
aclIpv6Name.description: The name of this IPv6 ACL entry, which must consist of 1 to 31 alphanumeric characters and uniquely identify this IPv6 ACL. An existing IPv6 ACL can be renamed by setting this object to a new name. This object must be set to complete a new IPv6 ACL row instance.

aclIpv6Status.name: aclIpv6Status
aclIpv6Status.description: Status of this instance. active(1) - this ACL instance is active createAndGo(4) - set to this value to create an instance destroy(6) - set to this value to delete an instance The aclMacName object must be set to complete this row instance.

aclIpv6RuleTable.name: aclIpv6RuleTable
aclIpv6RuleTable.description: A table of IPv6 ACL Rule instances.

aclIpv6RuleEntry.name: aclIpv6RuleEntry
aclIpv6RuleEntry.description: A table of IPv6 ACL Classification Rules

aclIpv6RuleIndex.name: aclIpv6RuleIndex
aclIpv6RuleIndex.description: The index of this rule instance within an IPv6 ACL.

aclIpv6RuleAction.name: aclIpv6RuleAction
aclIpv6RuleAction.description: The type of action this IPv6 ACL rule should perform.

aclIpv6RuleLogging.name: aclIpv6RuleLogging
aclIpv6RuleLogging.description: Flag to indicate that the ACL rule is being logged. A hardware count of the number of times this rule is hit is reported via the aclTrapRuleLogEvent notification. This object may be supported for an aclIPv6RuleAction setting of permit(1) and/or deny(2), depending on the ACL feature capabilities of the device.

aclIpv6RuleAssignQueueId.name: aclIpv6RuleAssignQueueId
aclIpv6RuleAssignQueueId.description: Queue identifier to which all inbound packets matching this ACL rule are directed. This object defaults to the standard queue assignment for user priority 0 traffic per the IEEE 802.1D specification based on the number of assignable queues in the system: 1-3 queues: 0 4-7 queues: 1 8 queues: 2 This default assignment is static and is not influenced by other system configuration changes.

aclIpv6RuleRedirectIntf.name: aclIpv6RuleRedirectIntf
aclIpv6RuleRedirectIntf.description: A non-zero value indicates the external ifIndex to which all inbound packets matching this Ipv6 ACL rule are directed. A value of zero means packet redirection is not in effect, which is the default value of this object. Note that packet redirection and mirroring (aclIpv6RuleMirrorIntf object) are mutually-exclusive rule attributes.

aclIpv6RuleMirrorIntf.name: aclIpv6RuleMirrorIntf
aclIpv6RuleMirrorIntf.description: A non-zero value indicates the external ifIndex to which all inbound packets matching this IPv6 ACL rule are copied. A value of zero means packet mirroring is not in effect, which is the default value of this object. Note that packet mirroring and redirection (aclIpv6RuleRedirectIntf object) are mutually-exclusive rule attributes.

aclIpv6RuleMatchEvery.name: aclIpv6RuleMatchEvery
aclIpv6RuleMatchEvery.description: Flag to indicate that the ACL rule is defined to match on every IP packet, regardless of content.

aclIpv6RuleProtocol.name: aclIpv6RuleProtocol
aclIpv6RuleProtocol.description: icmp - 1 igmp - 2 ip - 4 tcp - 6 udp - 17 All values from 1 to 255 are valid.

aclIpv6RuleSrcL4Port.name: aclIpv6RuleSrcL4Port
aclIpv6RuleSrcL4Port.description: The Source Port Number (Layer 4) used in the ACL Classification.

aclIpv6RuleSrcL4PortRangeStart.name: aclIpv6RuleSrcL4PortRangeStart
aclIpv6RuleSrcL4PortRangeStart.description: The Source Port Number(Layer 4) range start.

aclIpv6RuleSrcL4PortRangeEnd.name: aclIpv6RuleSrcL4PortRangeEnd
aclIpv6RuleSrcL4PortRangeEnd.description: The Source Port Number(Layer 4) range end.

aclIpv6RuleDestL4Port.name: aclIpv6RuleDestL4Port
aclIpv6RuleDestL4Port.description: The Destination Port (Layer 4) used in ACl classification.

aclIpv6RuleDestL4PortRangeStart.name: aclIpv6RuleDestL4PortRangeStart
aclIpv6RuleDestL4PortRangeStart.description: The Destination Port (Layer 4) starting range used in ACL classification.

aclIpv6RuleDestL4PortRangeEnd.name: aclIpv6RuleDestL4PortRangeEnd
aclIpv6RuleDestL4PortRangeEnd.description: The Destination Port (Layer 4) ending range used in ACL classification.

aclIpv6RuleStatus.name: aclIpv6RuleStatus
aclIpv6RuleStatus.description: Status of this instance. active(1) - this ACL Rule is active createAndGo(4) - set to this value to create an instance destroy(6) - set to this value to delete an instance

aclIpv6RuleFlowLabel.name: aclIpv6RuleFlowLabel
aclIpv6RuleFlowLabel.description: Flow label is 20-bit number that is unique to an IPv6 packet, used by end stations to signify quality-of-service handling in routers.

aclIpv6RuleIPDSCP.name: aclIpv6RuleIPDSCP
aclIpv6RuleIPDSCP.description: The Differentiated Services Code Point value.

aclRuleSrcIpv6Prefix.name: aclRuleSrcIpv6Prefix
aclRuleSrcIpv6Prefix.description: The Ipv6 Prefix Address configured on the Service Port.

aclRuleDstIpv6Prefix.name: aclRuleDstIpv6Prefix
aclRuleDstIpv6Prefix.description: The Ipv6 Prefix Address configured on the Service Port.

aclIpv6RuleTimeRangeName.name: aclIpv6RuleTimeRangeName
aclIpv6RuleTimeRangeName.description: Name of the time range, that the ACL rule has referenced.It must start with alphabet and shall consist of 1 to 31 alphanumeric characters.

aclIpv6RuleTimeRangeStatus.name: aclIpv6RuleTimeRangeStatus
aclIpv6RuleTimeRangeStatus.description: Flag that indicates the ACL rule status. If the status is active, it implies that the ACL rule is in effect. If the status is inactive, it implies that the ACL rule is not in effect.

aclIpv6RuleRateLimitCrate.name: aclIpv6RuleRateLimitCrate
aclIpv6RuleRateLimitCrate.description: Committed rate attribute statement value, specified in kbps.

aclIpv6RuleRateLimitCburst.name: aclIpv6RuleRateLimitCburst
aclIpv6RuleRateLimitCburst.description: Committed burst size attribute statement value, specified in kbytes.

aclIpv6RuleIcmpType.name: aclIpv6RuleIcmpType
aclIpv6RuleIcmpType.description: ACL rule matches on the specified ICMP type. All values from 1 to 255 are valid.

aclIpv6RuleIcmpCode.name: aclIpv6RuleIcmpCode
aclIpv6RuleIcmpCode.description: ACL rule matches on the specified ICMP code. All values from 1 to 255 are valid.

aclIpv6RuleRouting.name: aclIpv6RuleRouting
aclIpv6RuleRouting.description: Flag to indicate the ACL rule to match on packets with routing extention header

aclIpv6RuleFragments.name: aclIpv6RuleFragments
aclIpv6RuleFragments.description: Flag to indicate the ACL rule to match if the packets with fragments extention header

aclIpv6RuleEstablished.name: aclIpv6RuleEstablished
aclIpv6RuleEstablished.description: Flag to indicate the ACL rule to match on TCP packets that has either RST or ACK bits set in the TCP header

aclVlanTable.name: aclVlanTable
aclVlanTable.description: A table of ACL VLAN instances per direction.

aclVlanIndex.name: aclVlanIndex
aclVlanIndex.description: The Vlan to which this ACL instance applies.

aclVlanDirection.name: aclVlanDirection
aclVlanDirection.description: The Vlan direction to which this ACL instance applies.

aclVlanSequence.name: aclVlanSequence
aclVlanSequence.description: The relative evaluation sequence of this ACL for this Vlan and direction. When multiple ACLs are allowed for a given Vlan and direction, the sequence number determines the order in which the list of ACLs are evaluated, with lower sequence numbers given higher precedence. The sequence number value is arbitrary, but must be a unique non-zero value for a given Vlan and direction. Setting this object to an existing sequence number value for a given Vlan and direction causes the ACL corresponding to that value to be replaced with this ACL.

aclVlanAclType.name: aclVlanAclType
aclVlanAclType.description: The type of this ACL, which is used to interpret the aclVlanId object value. Each type of ACL uses its own numbering scheme for identification (see aclVlanAclId object for details). The aclVlanAclId object must be specified along with this object.

aclVlanAclId.name: aclVlanAclId
aclVlanAclId.description: The ACL identifier value, which is interpreted based on the aclVlanType object. For the IP ACLs, the actual ACL number is its identifier as follows: IP standard ranges from 1-99, while IP extended ranges from 100-199. Here, aclVlanAclId represents aclIndex. The MAC ACLs use an internally-generated index value that is assigned when the ACL is created. Here, aclVlanAclId represents aclMacIndex. The IPv6 ACLs use an internally-generated index value that is assigned when the ACL is created.Here, aclVlanAclId represents aclIpv6Index. The aclVlanType object must be specified along with this object.

aclVlanStatus.name: aclVlanStatus
aclVlanStatus.description: Status of this instance. active(1) - this ACL Vlan instance is active createAndGo(4) - set to this value to assign an ACL to a Vlan and direction destroy(6) - set to this value to remove an ACL from a Vlan and direction
